# Homeschool Hub — Project Rules

## Stack

- Mobile app: iOS + Android (match whatever framework is already in this codebase)
- Backend: Supabase (Postgres + Edge Functions)
- Never introduce new infrastructure without asking first

## Before writing any code on any task

1. State a short plan and list every file you will change
2. Wait for my explicit approval before writing a single line

## Code rules

- Make the smallest change that satisfies the task
- Do not refactor, rename, or reformat anything outside the files the task requires
- Match the folder structure, file naming, and import style of neighbouring files
- Match existing UI component and styling patterns — do not introduce new libraries
- Functional components with hooks only
- Student relationships use **student IDs**, never names
- Dates for calendar/events: `YYYY-MM-DD`
- Styling: StyleSheet + tokens in `constants/Colors.ts`, `constants/Typography.ts`
- Always use upsert with an explicit conflict target when writing to attendance,
  lesson_completions, or notification_log

## When uncertain

- Ask rather than assume
- If you're about to touch more than 3 files, stop and confirm with me first

